post_text: Last week our MSA-1 Reseda Principal joined Councilmember Bob Blumenfield for a social distancing groundbreaking of the Sherman Way Great Streets Project. This project focuses on revitalizing the City of Reseda and enriching the community. We're excited to be a part of #ResedaRising by continuing to provide an excellent program to the community of Reseda.
shared_text:
Councilmember Bob Blumenfield
May 19 at 7:30 AM ·

Last week I joined the community of Reseda for a social distancing groundbreaking of the Sherman Way Great Streets Project, a core component of the #ResedaRising initiative. This $3.5 million project will revitalize Reseda's commercial core and make Sherman Way between WIlbur and Lindley a more inviting place to visit, shop and dine. Watch the video below to learn more.

A special thanks to L.A. This Week for producing and thank you to all the participants in this groundbreaking, including the several members of the @Reseda Neighborhood Council, Principal Mustafa Sahin of Magnolia Science Academy, and Frank Bush, Reseda local and former General Manager of LA Department of Building and Safety.
